Product description

Amazon.ca Product Description

The original plasmacar by PlaSmart Inc. Red ride on toy, ages 3 yrs and up, No batteries, gears, or pedals, twist, turn, wiggle for endless fun

From the Manufacturer

It's like magic, but you don't need to be a magician to get it to work. The PlasmaCar is a mechanical marvel that makes use of that most inexhaustible of energy sources, kid-power, by harnessing the natural forces of inertia, centrifugal force, gravity, and friction. It's so easy to operate; all it needs is a driver and a smooth, flat surface. The PlasmaCar is adult-friendly, too. For starters, it doesn't require an expensive power source that needs constant replacement. No batteries, no power-cells, no liquid fuel-just the occasional cookie or two. It's quiet too-the only sound you'll hear is the sound of its wheels. It provides kids with plenty of exercise, more so than most toys. And the PlasmaCar is engineered to be absolutely safe when used appropriately. It's been extensively tested, and meets or exceeds all significant international safety standards. Fully Assembled: 31" x14" x 16"8.15 lbs Please look at the videos on the catalog for installation.

From the manufacturer

The Original PlasmaCar by PlaSmart Inc.

At a Glance:
  • Requires no batteries; moves via mechanical operation
  • Develops motor skills and provides exercise
  • Well-built design supports kids & adults up to 220 pounds
  • Quiet operation for indoor and outdoor use
  • Simple to put together with few tools required (assembly requires a rubber mallet, screwdriver, or 17 mm socket wrench)
What's in the Box?

Each box contains your Original PlasmaCar (assembly required), and instructions.

Twist, turn, wiggle for endless fun!

Simple, Fun Operation

The Original PlasmaCar is a well-designed toy that provides a thrill that belies its simple, colorful look. Driving around the house, maneuvering nooks and crannies, and going in reverse never lost its appeal to our testers. They were surprised by just how much speed the car was able to pick up considering it's manual operation. Our testers found the PlasmaCar rides best on hard, flat surfaces. Carpet, grass, gravel, and other 'rough' surfaces diminished the toy's ability to propel forward.

Develop Motor Skills While Having Fun

The PlasmaCar rewards good hand-eye coordination and fluid movements and provides a fun way for kids to get exercise while keeping occupied. As kids learn to drive faster and more precisely, they will be developing motor skills. Young children who have trouble propelling the car forward by steering can still have fun on the PlasmaCar by pushing off with their feet. Because it has no electronics or motor, this toy is pleasantly quiet making it appropriate for indoor and outdoor use.

Turn the Steering Wheel and Away You Go

Meets & exceeds US, Canadian & European safety standards.

CPSIA, CCPSA, ASTM & EN71 compliant; ISO & ICTI certified.

Ages 3 years and up; can reach an exhilarating 10 km/hour (6mph).

Features a patented safety seat; supports up to 220 lbs.

Winner of Red Tricycle's 2016 Totally Awesome Awards

Samantha T.
5.0 out of 5 stars Best toy ever
Reviewed in Canada on December 25, 2016
Colour Name: BlueVerified Purchase
We just put the kiddos- ages 2 years and 9 months - to bed this Christmas night and my husband has since, been playing with the plasma cars. While he found them enjoyable, he did have a couple of recommendations.

1) Please add a cushion. He is starting to feel his age and his keister is tender. Perhaps, it's the padded chairs at work - if he chose to sit in a plain plastic chair it would be easier but, for all your 25+ year old plasma car enthusiasts, a cushion option would be lovely.

2) They're too short. Now, they're a great height for the children who we bought them for - a perfect height, I'd say. My husband, however, is 5'7 and apparently, finds them too short. He has a cramp (so do I but it's in the form of a headache caused by trying not to laugh at him). He'd like an extra-tall option for the same enthusiasts who would like a cushion.

3) He would also like a motor - a little one, though (I'm so sorry, PlaSmart). Apparently, it is very difficult to get over the bumps in the floor and a motor would help him glide with ease. Personally, I think he could use the cardio workout but as he lay on the floor, holding his rump, cramped up from the short car and breathing heavily from the workout - perhaps, he should just accept that he should let the kids play with their own toys and he can go play with his PS4 instead!

Yes, there's my review - this thing is more fun than a PS4 and my husband is willing to cause himself bodily pain to glide across the floor yelling "wheeee", possibly waking up the true owners of these toys - the children. 100% worth every penny for such a great product!

JB
5.0 out of 5 stars Great car - will get years of play
Reviewed in Canada on July 28, 2016
Colour Name: RedVerified Purchase
Wonderful, sturdy car for my 1.5 yr old toddler. Can't beat the design & quality. We don't use ours inside on hardwood floors -- only outside on sidewalks, driveways, basketball courts, etc. She loves how fast it can go, and it gets her tons of exercise. She has tipped over on it, but only a few times, and it's not the car's fault - she loves to go (super) fast, and is learning how gravity works when you cut a turn too fast! When it does tip on her, it's lightweight enough that I don't have to worry about it hurting her, so it's the perfect way to learn, in my opinion. She adores this car, and I am confident she will continue to love it as she grows - a great investment considering how easily kids tire of pricey toys.

Putting it together on my own was fine, up until lining up the steering wheel to ensure it was on perfectly straight -- much easier if you have someone else there to help hold it steady.
